14 SECTION 2.
15 Chapter 1 of Title 31 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to general
16 provisions regarding health, is amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
17 "31-1-26.
18 (a) The department shall implement projects to increase education on and public awareness
19 of valvular heart disease, enhance the diagnosis and treatment of valvular heart disease, and
20 reduce the incidence of sudden cardiac death caused by valvular heart disease. Such
21 projects may be implemented by the department directly or through the award of grants or
22 contracts to public or nonprofit private entities. The department may provide technical
23 assistance with respect to the planning, development, and operation of such projects
24 directly or through such awards.
25 (b) The projects provided for in subsection (a) of this Code section may include projects
26 to initiate, increase, or improve:
27 (1) Education on and public awareness of the risk factors, symptoms, and public health
28 consequences of valvular heart disease;
29 (2) Diagnostic capabilities of physicians and other healthcare providers regarding
30 valvular heart disease and access to treatment for individuals with valvular heart disease;
31 and
32 (3) Surveillance programs to analyze and report on out-of-hospital cardiac arrests related
33 to valvular heart disease to improve patient outcomes.
34 (c) In awarding grants or contracts for projects pursuant to subsection (a) of this Code
35 section, the department shall give priority to projects that target populations most impacted
36 by valvular heart disease or that address health disparities in the risk factors, treatment, and
37 outcomes of valvular heart disease based on race, ethnicity, gender, and socioeconomic
38 status.
