39 (d) The department shall ensure that projects implemented pursuant to this Code section
40 are coordinated, as appropriate, with other state agencies that carry out activities regarding
41 valvular heart disease.
42 (e) The department shall:
43 (1) Collect and analyze the findings of research conducted with respect to valvular heart
44 disease; and
45 (2) Publish on the department's public website best practices for physicians and other
46 healthcare providers who provide care to individuals diagnosed with valvular heart
47 disease. Such information shall also be annually distributed by the Georgia Composite
48 Medical Board to all physicians licensed to practice medicine in this state."
49 SECTION 3.
50 This Act shall become effective upon its approval by the Governor or upon its becoming law
51 without such approval.
52 SECTION 4.
53 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
